<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1194.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Cape Haitien</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Troops of Government have just surprised and captured the forts
                            protecting the town and routed the rebels who are retreating into the
                            woods. Considerable firing in the streets at this moment.</p>
                        <p>French cruiser <hi rend="italic">Descartes</hi> entered port this morning
                            and sailors now patrolling town.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Livingston</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>